ickle. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Strain pickled vegetables through simmering basket over a jug, reserving pickling liquid. Transfer vegetables into a serving bowl and set aside until ready to serve."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Prosciutto batons"},{"content":"Preheat oven to 200°C. Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper, then line a plate with paper towel and set aside."},{"content":"Roll each of the 8 slices of prosciutto lengthways over skewers to form long, thin tubes. Place skewers onto prepared baking tray and bake for 6 minutes (200°C). Transfer onto prepared plate to cool, then remove skewers from prosciutto (it will become crispy as it cools)."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Cocktail mix"},{"content":"Place a heavy-based chargrill pan over high heat. Add jalapeños and chargrill, turning, until charred on all sides."},{"content":"Place salt and chargrilled jalapeños into mixing bowl and blend <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and blend <b>3 sec\/speed 9<b>."},{"content":"Add tomato juice, lime juice, mezcal, ice, smoked paprika and 1 tablespoon of the reserved pickling liquid, then blend <b>45 sec\/speed 9<b>."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Place salt and chilli powder onto a plate and stir to combine. Lightly rub 1 lime quarter around rim of each serving glass, then dip rims into chilli salt."},{"content":"Place ice into each glass and top with Bloody Maria. Garnish with prosciutto batons and serve immediately with pickled vegetables and limes."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Use leftover pickled vegetables in tacos and burritos.","You can replace jalapeños with long green chillies and white wine vinegar with rice vinegar.","<strong>Virgin bloody Maria<\/strong>: Replace the mezcal with soda water for a non-alcoholic cocktail."],"basicInfo":["easy","45m","2h 45m","8 portions"]}